                        Caffery
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1947v03</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d175</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">175</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1947-06-29T10:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1947-06-29T10:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-06-29T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-06-29T10:00:00-05:00" n="175" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d175">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.50 Recovery/6–2947: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-06-29T16:00:00+01:00">June 29, 1947—4 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2590. Bidault told me this morning he is very “uncertain”. “Molotov”, he said,
                    “clearly does not wish this business to succeed but on the other hand his hungry
                    satellites are smacking their lips in expectation of getting some of your money.
                    He is obviously embarrassed”.</p>
                <p>Bevin told me this morning he is not optimistic. “Molotov is dragging his feet.
                    However Bidault and I gave him to understand yesterday that we are determined in
                    one way or another to go ahead with this with or without him”.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
